Julia is a high-level, high-performance dynamic programming language for technical computing, with syntax that is familiar to users of other technical computing environments. 

http://julialang.org/

An Emacs mode for editing Julia code, called `julia-mode', is part of the Julia: https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia-emacs/blob/master/julia-mode.el

EmacsSpeaksStatistics also features Julia support.

A blog post about editing Julia code with Emacs http://www.wilfred.me.uk/blog/2014/11/16/editing-julia-code-with-emacs/

